        %h1 .removeClass()
      #removeClass1{"data-role" => "content", "data-theme" => "c"}
        %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
          %span.name .removeClass( [ className ] )
          %span.returns
            Returns:
            %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#jQuery"} jQuery
        .entry-details
          %p.desc
            %strong> Description:
            Remove a single class, multiple classes, or all classes from each element in the set of matched elements.
          %ul.signatures
            %li#removeClass-className.signature
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.0/"} 1.0
                \.removeClass( [ className ] )
              %p.arguement
                %strong> className
                A class name to be removed from the class attribute of each matched element.
            %li.signature{:id => "removeClass-functionindex, class"}
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.4/"} 1.4
                \.removeClass( function(index, class) )
              %p.arguement
                %strong> function(index, class)
                A function returning one or more space-separated class names to be removed. Receives the index position of the element in the set and the old class value as arguments.
          .longdesc
            %p If a class name is included as a parameter, then only that class will be removed from the set of matched elements. If no class names are specified in the parameter, all classes will be removed.
            %p More than one class may be removed at a time, separated by a space, from the set of matched elements, like so:
            %pre
              :preserve
                $('p').removeClass('myClass yourClass')
            %p
              This method is often used with
              %code .addClass()
              to switch elements' classes from one to another, like so:
            %pre
              :preserve
                $('p').removeClass('myClass noClass').addClass('yourClass');
            %p
              Here, the
              %code myClass
              and
              %code noClass
              classes are removed from all paragraphs, while
              %code yourClass
              is added.
            %p
              To replace all existing classes with another class, we can use
              %code .attr('class', 'newClass')
              instead.
            %p
              As of jQuery 1.4, the
              %code .removeClass()
              method allows us to indicate the class to be removed by passing in a function.
            %pre
              :preserve
                $('li:last').removeClass(function() {
                          return $(this).prev().attr('class');
                        });            %p
              This example removes the class name of the penultimate
              %code &lt;li&gt;
              from the last
              = succeed "." do
                %code &lt;li&gt;
          %h3 Examples:
          #entry-examples.entry-examples
